---
description: Content architecture — site data, MDX blog fetching, private content repo
globs: lib/**/*.js,content/**/*,scripts/**/*.js
---

- `lib/data.js` is the single source of truth for site-wide structured
  content (nav, sponsors, directors, chapters, advisors, contact info,
  recommendation letters). Add new structured content there rather than
  hardcoding it in page files — see `nextjs-app-router.mdc`.
- `content/blog/` is populated at build/dev time by
  `scripts/fetch-blog-content.js`, which pulls MDX posts from the **private**
  `mllws/mllws-blog` repo using the `BLOG_CONTENT_TOKEN` env var. It is
  gitignored — never commit files into `content/blog/`, and never remove it
  from `.gitignore`. Draft posts must never end up in this (public) repo's
  git history.
- Blog post access goes through `lib/posts.js` (`getAllPosts`,
  `getPostBySlug`, `getAllTags` — see `docs/specs/mdx-blog-fetching.md` for
  the full spec). Pages should import from there, not read `content/blog/`
  directly.
- Anything touching `content/blog/` or the fetch step must fail safe: a
  missing `BLOG_CONTENT_TOKEN`, an empty directory, or one malformed post
  must never crash `npm run dev` or `npm run build` — log and continue
  rather than throw.
